  "text": "In general, a rational B-spline in R d is the projection onto d-dimensional physical space of a polynomial B-spline defined in (d+1)-dimensional homogeneous coordinate space. For a complete discussion, see the book by Farin [CITATION_1] and the references therein. In this way, a great variety of geometrical entities can be constructed and, in particular, all conic sections in physical space can be obtained exactly. To obtain a NURBS curve in R 2 , we start introducing the NURBS basis functions of degree p,",
